originalText.text: The Rabbi and Rebbetzin are great. I enjoy spending time at the synagogue.

text.text: The Rabbi and Rebbetzin are great. I enjoy spending time at the synagogue.

originalText.text:
Great shul, services, and with such a warm community.  They have a number of community events and and connected to a great pre-school and day camp for children.

They are open to everyone in the community, and I can not express how thankful we are for all they have done for our children.

originalText.text:
Beis Shlomo Zalmen is where three of my grandchidren attended preschool
and the school should be recognized for their superior educational and caring approaches to teaching.  Furthermore, my grandchildren really liked it and came home everyday with cheerful stories and astonishment at what they had learned.  Often they said " Look Grandma--see what I did."

originalText.text: In the shadow of the Wiiliamsburg Bridge, this plain red brick shul is a really nice place to daven if you are in the area.  Lutowiska was a village to the East of Krakow, Poland, present day Ukraine. Led by Rabbi Horowitz, shlit"a. Photos can be seen in the book, "Ten Times Chai: 180 Orthodox Synagogues of New York City."
